Package nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.request

Class RequestSenderOfHttpClient

java.lang.Object
nusri.fyp.demo.roboflow.request.RequestSenderOfHttpClient
All Implemented Interfaces:
RequestSender
@Component @Deprecated public class RequestSenderOfHttpClient extends Object implements RequestSender
Deprecated.
Can not pass test.
Implementation of the RequestSender interface using the HttpClient for sending HTTP requests asynchronously.
This class handles both POST and GET requests to the Roboflow API and processes the responses using CompletableFuture.
It is deprecated in favor of a newer, more efficient HTTP client implementation.
Since:
1.0

      Deprecated.
      Asynchronously sends a POST request to the Roboflow API.
      If data is provided, it is serialized and sent as the body of the request.
      If no data is provided, the request is sent with no body.
      Specified by:
      postAsync in interface RequestSender
      Parameters:
      BASE_URI - The URI to which the POST request will be sent.
      log - The logger used to log request information.
      data - The request data to be sent (can be null).
      success - The class type of the expected success response.
      failure - The class type of the expected failure response (can be null).
      requestClass - The class type of the request data (can be null).
      Returns:
      A CompletableFuture containing the response data.
